<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1285,502,555]" box="[151,1285,533,555]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<typeStatus box="[151,201,534,555]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="G. Canestrini, 1881" authorityName="G. Canestrini" authorityYear="1881" box="[287,688,533,555]" class="Arachnida" family="Parasitidae" genus="Gamasus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pectinifer">
<emphasis box="[287,484,533,555]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Gamasus pectinifer</emphasis>
G. 
<bibRefCitation author="Canestrini" box="[518,688,533,555]" firstAuthor="Canestrini" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="1077 - 1086" refId="ref39536" refString="Canestrini, G. &amp; Canestrini, R. (1881) Nuove specie del genere Gamasus. Atti del Reale Istituto Veneto di Scienze, Lettere ed Arti (Series 5), 7, 1077 - 1086 + Plate VIII." type="journal article" year="1881">Canestrini, 1881</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, by subsequent designation (
<bibRefCitation author="Berlese" box="[979,1123,533,555]" firstAuthor="Berlese" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="299 - 474" refId="ref38913" refString="Berlese, A. (1904) Illustrazione iconografica degli Acari mirmecofili. Redia, 1, 299 - 474 + Plates VII - XX." type="journal article" year="1904">Berlese, 1904</bibRefCitation>
), but see below.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1436,599,1560]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
The 
<typeStatus box="[208,256,600,624]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1888" box="[401,552,599,624]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Pachylaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[401,552,599,624]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Pachylaelaps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is always said to be 
<taxonomicName authority="G. Canestrini, 1881" authorityName="G. Canestrini" authorityYear="1881" box="[824,1295,599,624]" class="Arachnida" family="Parasitidae" genus="Gamasus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pectinifer">
<emphasis box="[824,1048,599,624]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Gamasus pectinifer</emphasis>
G. 
<bibRefCitation author="Canestrini" box="[1100,1295,599,624]" firstAuthor="Canestrini" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="1077 - 1086" refId="ref39536" refString="Canestrini, G. &amp; Canestrini, R. (1881) Nuove specie del genere Gamasus. Atti del Reale Istituto Veneto di Scienze, Lettere ed Arti (Series 5), 7, 1077 - 1086 + Plate VIII." type="journal article" year="1881">Canestrini, 1881</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but that is impossible. The genus name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1888" box="[495,646,636,661]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Pachylaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[495,646,636,661]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Pachylaelaps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was first used by 
<bibRefCitation author="Berlese" box="[871,1048,636,661]" firstAuthor="Berlese" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="171 - 222" refId="ref38685" refString="Berlese, A. (1888 b) Acari austro-americani quos collegit Aloysius Balzan. Manipulus primus. Species novas circiter quinquaginta complectens. Bolletino della Societa Entomologica Italiana, 20, 171 - 222 + Plates 5 - 13." type="journal article" year="1888" yearSuffix="b">Berlese (1888b</bibRefCitation>
, 30 November, date from 
<bibRefCitation author="Poggi" firstAuthor="Poggi" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="157 - 188" refId="ref44498" refString="Poggi, R. (2008) Le date di stampa dei periodici editi dalla Societa Entomologica Italiana dal 1869 al 2007. Memorie della Societa Entomologica Italiana, 87, 157 - 188. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.4081 / memoriesei. 2008.157" type="journal article" year="2008">Poggi, 2008</bibRefCitation>
), with two included species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Berlese, 1888" authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1888" box="[541,940,671,696]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Pachylaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haeros">
<emphasis box="[541,775,671,696]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Pachylaelaps haeros</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Berlese, A." bookContentInfo="17 text pages + Plates 1 - 10" box="[784,940,671,696]" journalOrPublisher="Junk, The Hague" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" part="51" refId="ref38645" refString="Berlese, A. (1888 a) Acari, Myriopoda et Scorpiones hucusque in Italia reperta, 51, 17 text pages + Plates 1 - 10. (Reprint by Junk, The Hague, 1979)." title="Acari, Myriopoda et Scorpiones hucusque in Italia reperta" type="book" year="1888">Berlese, 1888</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Berlese, 1888" authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1888" box="[997,1432,671,696]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Pachylaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="athleticus">
<emphasis box="[997,1265,671,696]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Pachylaelaps athleticus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Berlese, A." bookContentInfo="17 text pages + Plates 1 - 10" box="[1274,1432,671,696]" journalOrPublisher="Junk, The Hague" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" part="51" refId="ref38645" refString="Berlese, A. (1888 a) Acari, Myriopoda et Scorpiones hucusque in Italia reperta, 51, 17 text pages + Plates 1 - 10. (Reprint by Junk, The Hague, 1979)." title="Acari, Myriopoda et Scorpiones hucusque in Italia reperta" type="book" year="1888">Berlese, 1888</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[202,250,708,732]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">type</typeStatus>
species of the genus must therefore be either 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1888" box="[766,869,708,733]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Pachylaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haeros">
<emphasis box="[766,780,709,732]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[794,869,708,733]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">haeros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1888" box="[908,1045,708,733]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Pachylaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="athleticus">
<emphasis box="[908,922,709,732]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[936,1045,708,733]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">athleticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, 1802" authorityName="G. Canestrini" authorityYear="1881" box="[1060,1278,708,733]" class="Arachnida" family="Parasitidae" genus="Gamasus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pectinifer">
<emphasis box="[1060,1278,708,733]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Gamasus pectinifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cannot be the 
<typeStatus box="[151,199,744,768]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">type</typeStatus>
species of the genus because it was not one of the species originally included when the genus was described (
<emphasis box="[160,697,780,805]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">International Code of Zoological Nomenclature</emphasis>
, Article 67.2). Only ten days later 
<bibRefCitation author="Berlese" box="[1092,1264,780,805]" firstAuthor="Berlese" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" refId="ref38645" refString="Berlese, A. (1888 a) Acari, Myriopoda et Scorpiones hucusque in Italia reperta, 51, 17 text pages + Plates 1 - 10. (Reprint by Junk, The Hague, 1979)." type="book" year="1888" yearSuffix="a">Berlese (1888a</bibRefCitation>
, 10 December) redescribed the genus and added a third species, &quot; 
<emphasis box="[749,946,816,839]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Gamase Savignii</emphasis>
&quot;, apparently referring to 
<taxonomicName authority="Audouin, 1826" authorityName="Audouin" authorityYear="1826" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Acarus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="savignyi">
<emphasis box="[1251,1435,816,839]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Acarus savignyi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Audouin" box="[151,328,852,877]" firstAuthor="Audouin" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="99 - 186" refId="ref38460" refString="Audouin, V. (1826) Explication sommaire des planches arachnides de l'Egypte et de la Syrie. In: Savigny, J. C. (Ed.) Description de l'Egypte ou Recueil des Observations et des Recherches qui ont ete Faites en Egypte Pendant l'Expedition de l'Armee Francaise, Volume 8, Histoire Naturelle I, C. L. F. Panckoucke, Paris, pp. 99 - 186." type="book chapter" year="1826">Audouin, 1826</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Berlese" box="[342,525,852,877]" firstAuthor="Berlese" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" refId="ref38806" refString="Berlese, A. (1892 c) Acari, Myriopoda et Scorpiones hucusque in Italia reperta. Ordo Mesostigmata (Gamasidae). (Sumptibus Auctoris, Patavii). 143 pp." type="book" year="1892" yearSuffix="c">Berlese (1892c)</bibRefCitation>
then moved 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1888" box="[685,793,852,877]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Pachylaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haeros">
<emphasis box="[685,699,853,876]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[718,793,852,877]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">haeros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1888" box="[857,999,852,877]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Pachylaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="athleticus">
<emphasis box="[857,871,853,876]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[890,999,852,877]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">athleticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
into his new subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Pachylaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Megalolaelaps">
<emphasis box="[1285,1436,852,877]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Pachylaelaps</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[160,326,887,912]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Megalolaelaps</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
, and placed 
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, 1802" authorityName="G. Canestrini" authorityYear="1881" box="[505,652,887,912]" class="Arachnida" family="Parasitidae" genus="Gamasus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pectinifer">
<emphasis box="[505,522,888,911]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[545,652,887,912]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">pectinifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName authority="(Pachylaelaps)" box="[707,1045,887,912]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Pachylaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Pachylaelaps">
<emphasis box="[707,858,887,912]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Pachylaelaps</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[883,1034,887,912]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Pachylaelaps</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
. This arrangement would make 
<taxonomicName authority="" box="[151,495,924,949]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Pachylaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Megalolaelaps">
<emphasis box="[151,302,924,949]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Pachylaelaps</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[319,485,924,949]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Megalolaelaps</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
an objective junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Pachylaelaps)" box="[868,1198,924,949]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Pachylaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Pachylaelaps">
<emphasis box="[868,1019,924,949]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Pachylaelaps</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1036,1187,924,949]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Pachylaelaps</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Berlese" box="[1212,1379,924,949]" firstAuthor="Berlese" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="299 - 474" refId="ref38913" refString="Berlese, A. (1904) Illustrazione iconografica degli Acari mirmecofili. Redia, 1, 299 - 474 + Plates VII - XX." type="journal article" year="1904">Berlese (1904)</bibRefCitation>
then re-described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1888" box="[299,450,959,984]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Pachylaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[299,450,959,984]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Pachylaelaps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
yet again, and stated that its 
<typeStatus box="[794,842,960,984]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">type</typeStatus>
species was 
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, 1802" authorityName="G. Canestrini" authorityYear="1881" box="[996,1132,959,984]" class="Arachnida" family="Parasitidae" genus="Gamasus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pectinifer">
<emphasis box="[996,1010,961,984]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1026,1132,959,984]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">pectinifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. That invalid 
<typeStatus box="[1297,1345,960,984]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">type</typeStatus>
species designation has been followed ever since. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1888" box="[628,862,996,1021]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Pachylaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haeros">
<emphasis box="[628,862,996,1021]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Pachylaelaps haeros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1888" box="[918,1056,996,1021]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Pachylaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="athleticus">
<emphasis box="[918,932,997,1020]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[947,1056,996,1021]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">athleticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are both now placed in the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1892" box="[151,317,1031,1056]" class="Arachnida" family="Megalolaelapidae" genus="Megalolaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,317,1031,1056]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Megalolaelaps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is the 
<typeStatus box="[479,527,1032,1056]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">type</typeStatus>
genus of the family 
<taxonomicName box="[766,969,1031,1056]" class="Arachnida" family="Megalolaelapidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Megalolaelapidae</taxonomicName>
. The use of either of these species as the 
<typeStatus box="[151,199,1068,1092]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1888" box="[322,473,1068,1093]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Pachylaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[322,473,1068,1093]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Pachylaelaps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
would seriously disrupt the taxonomic concept of the genus, which has been stable for over 100 years. We therefore maintain the current usage of 
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, 1802" authorityName="G. Canestrini" authorityYear="1881" box="[822,958,1103,1128]" class="Arachnida" family="Parasitidae" genus="Gamasus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pectinifer">
<emphasis box="[822,836,1105,1128]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[850,958,1103,1128]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">pectinifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the 
<typeStatus box="[1038,1086,1104,1128]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1888" box="[1214,1365,1103,1128]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Pachylaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1214,1365,1103,1128]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Pachylaelaps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the interest of stability.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1436,599,1560]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Further re-descriptions of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1888" box="[497,648,1175,1200]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Pachylaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[497,648,1175,1200]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Pachylaelaps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Evans &amp; Hyatt" box="[862,1116,1175,1200]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="118 - 129" refId="ref40346" refString="Evans, G. O. &amp; Hyatt, K. H. (1956) British mites of the genus Pachylaelaps Berlese (Gamasina - Pachylaelaptidae). Entomologist's Monthly Magazine, 92, 118 - 129." type="journal article" year="1956">Evans &amp; Hyatt (1956)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Costa" box="[1129,1275,1175,1200]" firstAuthor="Costa" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="253 - 277" refId="ref39861" refString="Costa, M. (1971) Mites of the genus Pachylaelaps Berlese (Acari: Mesostigmata, Pachylaelapidae) from litter in Israel. Israel Journal of Zoology, 20, 253 - 277." type="journal article" year="1971">
<collectingRegion box="[1129,1193,1175,1200]" country="Tanzania" name="Pwani" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Costa</collectingRegion>
(1971)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Koroleva" firstAuthor="Koroleva" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="411 - 483" refId="ref42472" refString="Koroleva, E. V. (1977 b) Family Pachylaelaptidae Vitzthum, 1931. In: Ghilyarov, M. S. &amp; Bregetova, N. G. (Eds) Key to the Soil Inhabiting Mites. Mesostigmata, Nauka, Leningrad, pp. 411 - 483." type="book chapter" year="1977" yearSuffix="b">Koroleva (1977b)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Masan" box="[254,423,1212,1237]" firstAuthor="Masan" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" refId="ref43485" refString="Masan, P. (2007 a) A Review of the Family Pachylaelapidae in Slovakia, with Systematics and Ecology of European Species (Acari: Mesostigmata: Eviphidoidea). Institute of Zoology, Slovak Academy of Sciences, Bratislava, 247 pp." type="book" year="2007" yearSuffix="a">Mašán (2007a)</bibRefCitation>
clarified the concept of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1888" box="[812,963,1212,1237]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Pachylaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[812,963,1212,1237]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Pachylaelaps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by removing some species that obviously belong in other genera (e.g. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1904" box="[462,603,1247,1272]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Onchodellus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[462,603,1247,1272]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Onchodellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Masan" authorityYear="2007" box="[617,754,1247,1272]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Pachydellus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[617,754,1247,1272]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Pachydellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and described the new subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Masan" authorityYear="2007" box="[1141,1354,1247,1272]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Pachylaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Longipachylaelaps">
<emphasis box="[1141,1354,1247,1272]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Longipachylaelaps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which may be easily separated from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1888" box="[498,649,1284,1309]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Pachylaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis box="[498,649,1284,1309]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Pachylaelaps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[658,719,1284,1307]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by the presence of normal needle-like clunal setae J5 (minute microsetae in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1888" box="[320,471,1319,1344]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Pachylaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis box="[320,471,1319,1344]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Pachylaelaps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[483,549,1319,1344]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
) and only one pair of hypertrophied slit-like gland openings gdS4 on the posterolateral margin of the dorsal shield (two pairs gdZ1 and gdS 
<quantity box="[894,937,1356,1381]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.016" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" unit="in" value="4.0">4 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1888" box="[943,1094,1356,1381]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Pachylaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis box="[943,1094,1356,1381]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Pachylaelaps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1101,1163,1356,1381]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1436,599,1560]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1888" box="[201,352,1391,1416]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Pachylaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[201,352,1391,1416]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Pachylaelaps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be now easily identified by the following characters: (1) sperm access system of females associated with coxae IV (
<figureCitation box="[444,513,1428,1453]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1483,1506]" captionTargetBox="[207,1376,576,1435]" captionTargetId="figure-633@9.[191,1392,561,1447]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Pachylaelapidae species, females, coxae III and IV showing attachment of sperm induction tubes. 1. Onchodellus slovacus; 2. Pachydellus sculptus; 3. Olopachys suecicus; 4. Pachylaelaps longulus. Based on Mašán (2007a)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5047865" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5047865/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
); (2) female tarsus II with two spur-like distal setae, pl1 and pl2; (3) genu I with 13 setae; and (4) tibial projections on male palp present (except for species of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="G. Canestrini" baseAuthorityYear="1881" box="[1045,1315,1463,1488]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Pachylaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pectinifer">
<emphasis box="[1045,1315,1463,1488]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Pachylaelaps pectinifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group). It currently comprises up to 60 known species found mostly in the Palaearctic Region, and only rarely in Africa, North America, 
<collectingCountry box="[333,436,1535,1560]" name="Australia" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Australia</collectingCountry>
and South Pacific Islands.
</paragraph>
